"Being born in this world is hardly to be borne,"' Luzhin senior dictated steadily, strolling back and forth about the schoolroom. 'Being born in this world is hardly to be borne.' And his son wrote, practically lying on the table and baring his teeth in their metallic scaffolding, and simply left blanks for the words 'born' and 'borne'. Arithmetic went better; there was myst